			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2016</a> paper:</span><br><i>Object-Oriented Design Pattern for DSL Program Monitoring</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/ZoéDrey.html">Zoé Drey</a>, <a href="../profile/CiprianTeodorov.html">Ciprian Teodorov</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/2997364.2997373">10.1145/2997364.2997373</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4d.html"><span class="tagM">T4D: Interpretation</span></a><ul><li> It introduces runtime monitoring support for programs written in DSLs.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> The monitoring approach is positioned in the context of DSL development and execution.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5g.html"><span class="tagL">T5G: Traceability</span></a><ul><li> Monitoring relies on collecting/relating execution information, akin to traceability between DSL constructs and runtime events.
</li></ul></li></ul>
